<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world]]></title><link/> https://www.wsj.com/news/world <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/wsj/en-us/world" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 7 月 29 日星期六 18:09:18 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Son of Colombian President Arrested on Money Laundering Charges]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>总检察长办公室表示正在调查尼古拉斯·佩特罗在其父亲竞选总统期间从毒贩那里收受金钱的指控<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001096144"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826315?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">古斯塔沃·佩特罗 (Gustavo Petro) 和他的儿子尼古拉斯 (Nicolás) 于 2014 年拍摄，当时佩特罗担任哥伦比亚波哥大市长。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：eitan abramovich/法新社/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001096144"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/kejal-vyas" itemprop="url" rel="author">凯贾尔·维亚斯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 29 日下午 1:14 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/son-of-colombian-president-arrested-on-money-laundering-charges-a45d630b"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>哥伦比亚波哥大——哥伦比亚当局表示，他们周六早些时候逮捕了总统古斯塔沃·佩特罗的长子，作为对他在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/former-colombia-rebel-gustavo-petro-inaugurated-as-president-11659917654?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">去年总统竞选</a>期间从毒贩那里收受金钱的指控进行更广泛调查的一部分。</p><p>总检察长办公室表示，来自哥伦比亚北部的地区政客尼古拉斯·佩特罗被指控洗钱和非法致富。记者未能联系到佩特罗的律师置评。尼古拉斯·佩特罗此前否认有不当行为。</p><p>逮捕行动是在检察官三月份表示他们已开始调查，指控年轻的佩特罗收受被定罪的毒品走私者的资金用于竞选活动，以换取他们参与政府所谓的全面和平倡议，这是总统谈判裁军的旗舰努力与主要犯罪集团和左翼叛乱分子打交道。</p><p>佩特罗总统是一名<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/with-new-colombian-president-the-left-surges-in-latin-america-11655828410?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">前叛军出身的政治家</a>，一年前因承诺打击腐败而上任。他称这些指控让他作为一名父亲感到痛苦，但表示他不会干涉此案。</p><p> “对于我的儿子，我祝他好运和力量，”总统在 X（该平台以前称为 Twitter）上发帖说。 “愿这些事件增强他的性格，让他反思自己的错误。”</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>政府表示，佩特罗并不知道任何涉嫌向尼古拉斯·佩特罗付款的事情，并且本应提供给他的任何资金都没有用于总统竞选。政府还表示，没有任何武装团体从与年轻的佩特罗的任何所谓交易中受益。</p><p>这次逮捕是在周二与民族解放军（一支长达 60 年的左翼叛乱组织）达成停火协议之前进行的，这对于总统紧张的全面和平计划来说是一个突破。对其他武装团体指挥官的逮捕令已被解除，以促使他们进行解除武装谈判，以换取对其罪行的减刑。</p><p> “我的政府不会向犯罪分子提供好处以换取贿赂，”总统在三月份针对他儿子的指控首次公开后表示。</p><p>总统上任的第一年充满动荡。 Invamer 6 月份的民意调查显示，他的支持率为 33.8%，低于 11 月份的 50%。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombias-president-replaces-market-friendly-finance-minister-in-cabinet-reshuffle-4dd9b67f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">由于内阁改组，包括负责经济、医疗保健和能源事务的部长在内的</a>多位部长辞职，医疗保健、劳工、 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombia-election-weighs-on-future-of-oil-sector-11655397102?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">养老金</a>和其他领域的几项大规模改革陷入停滞。联合国和美国官员表示，该国古柯作物（用于制造可卡因的植物）的规模<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombias-acreage-of-coca-used-to-make-cocaine-surges-to-record-11666306614?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">已经扩大</a>。</p><p>今年早些时候，佩特罗总统对儿子的前妻戴苏里斯·德尔·卡门·巴斯克斯 (Daysuris del Carmen Vásquez) 的调查表示欢迎。</p>告诉哥伦比亚《Semana》杂志，年轻的佩特罗在总统竞选期间从那些希望在总统的和平努力中获得优惠待遇的人士那里获得了大约 20 万美元。<p></p><p>巴斯克斯表示，总统并不知道这些交易，而且这些钱都存放在他们家的保险箱里。尼古拉斯·佩特罗否认了前妻的指控。</p><p>总检察长表示，巴斯克斯和年轻的佩特罗均于周六上午因洗钱指控被捕，调查人员仍在继续调查。</p><p>阿莱特·弗雷娅·卡拉奥,</p>巴斯克斯的一名律师表示，他对她被拘留感到惊讶，因为他的当事人正是提出指控并导致检察官展开调查的人。弗雷贾表示，他正在等待有关指控的更多细节，并拒绝进一步置评，直到巴斯克斯出庭受审。<p></p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——珍妮·卡罗莱纳·冈萨雷斯对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 Kejal Vyas： <a href="mailto:kejal.vyas@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">kejal.vyas@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 29 Jul 2023 17:14:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/son-of-colombian-president-arrested-on-money-laundering-charges-a45d630b</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/son-of-colombian-president-arrested-on-money-laundering-charges-a45d630b<author><![CDATA[Kejal Vyas]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>毒品贩运/交易</category><category>洗钱</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩运/走私</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>尼古拉·佩特罗</category><category>古斯塔沃·佩特罗</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>贩毒</category><category>交易</category><category>洗钱</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩卖</category><category>走私</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Niger Faces EU, U.S. Aid Cuts Following Military Takeover]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>欧洲已经冻结了援助，如果军方保留西非反恐盟友的权力，美国可能会效仿<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001095827"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=9B8EB2F8-7751-46ED-8D36-E964233A2505&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fblinken-says-u-s-aid-to-niger-in-jeopardy-following-coup-766a0156&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">国务卿安东尼·布林肯周六表示，尼日尔的军事政变危及了美国价值数亿美元的援助和安全支持。欧盟还暂停了与尼日尔的安全合作和财政支持。照片：达伦·英格兰/Shutterstock<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001095827"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/vivian-salama" itemprop="url" rel="author">Vivian Salama</a></span> ，<span class="author" itemprop="name">澳大利亚</span>布里斯班， <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/gabriele-steinhauser" itemprop="url" rel="author">Gabriele Steinhauser</a></span>和约翰内斯堡</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 29 日上午 9:42（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/blinken-says-u-s-aid-to-niger-in-jeopardy-following-coup-766a0156"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>欧盟周六冻结了对尼日尔的部分援助，美国表示，在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-general-declares-himself-leader-as-russian-mercenary-hails-coup-d47efa68?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">这个西非国家本周发生政变</a>后，其援助面临危险。尼日尔一直是西方在打击伊斯兰武装分子和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kremlins-wagner-shake-up-rattles-nerves-in-africa-middle-east-8c917a97" target="_blank" class="icon none">俄罗斯侵犯</a>该国领土方面的亲密盟友。地区。</p><p>这些公告是国际运动的一部分，旨在向尼日尔军方施压，要求释放该国民选总统穆罕默德·巴祖姆并恢复其权力。但限制<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-pledges-aid-for-niger-other-sahel-nations-5c5ae8bf?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">西方对尼日尔的支持</a>也有可能伤害该国 2600 万人民（世界上最贫穷的国家之一）以及近年来在非洲萨赫勒地区杀害数千人<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sahel-based-militants-edging-south-toward-west-africas-most-stable-and-prosperous-states-11646221800?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">的伊斯兰国和基地组织恐怖分子的</a>战斗。</p><p>欧盟外交政策负责人何塞普·博雷尔宣布，欧盟已冻结对尼日尔的预算支持和军事援助，以应对<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/apparent-coup-attempt-hits-u-s-ally-niger-e3efa36d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">叛乱</a>，并将继续承认巴祖姆为该国唯一合法总统。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826303?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">尼日尔有 2600 万人口，属于世界上最贫困的国家之一。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>美国国务卿安东尼·布林肯在访问澳大利亚期间也表达了对巴祖姆的支持，并警告说，如果尼日尔军方继续掌权，华盛顿可能会削减对尼日尔的支持。</p><p>布林肯说：“事实仍然是，我们所提供的非常重要的援助正在给尼日尔人民的生活带来实质性改变，但显然处于危险之中。” “我们已尽可能清楚地向那些破坏宪法秩序的人传达了这一点。”</p><p>布林肯没有将尼日尔发生的事件描述为一场政变，根据美国法律，政变将立即冻结援助。他是在与巴祖姆进行电话交谈后发表上述言论的。自周三早些时候以来，巴祖姆一直被关押在尼日尔首都尼亚美的住所中。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826301?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">穆罕默德·巴祖姆（去年拍摄）当选为 2021 年尼日尔总统。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：卢多维奇·马林/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>自2012年以来，美国已花费超过5亿美元来建设和训练尼日尔武装部队。这个幅员辽阔的西非国家驻有美国无人机和美国突击队，他们除了进行训练外，还为尼日尔特种部队在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-upends-u-s-security-plans-in-west-africa-handing-russia-an-opportunity-8dcf6679?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">打击叛乱分子的战斗任务</a>中提供建议。</p><p>欧盟还在尼日尔派驻了培训团。博雷尔宣布的冻结影响了该使命以及欧盟计划在 2021 年至 2024 年间向尼日尔预算和针对人口的项目提供的 5.03 亿欧元（约合 5.54 亿美元）的大部分资金。将继续向尼日尔提供人道主义援助，2023 年预算为 2500 万欧元。</p><p>武装分子对平民和基础设施的袭击导致萨赫勒地区数百万人流离失所，并导致世界粮食计划署所说的该地区前所未有的饥饿危机。据世界粮食计划署称，去年，近五分之一的尼日尔人没有足够的食物来维持他们的生活和生计。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="394" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826300?width=700&amp;height=394" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">本周末，关于谁在管理尼日尔及其首都尼亚美的问题仍然存在。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：STRINGER/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>西方官员担心，除了削弱对恐怖分子的打击之外，军事接管将使俄罗斯更容易扩大其在撒哈拉以南半干旱地带萨赫勒的影响力。尼日尔的邻国马里在 2021 年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-wagner-group-mercenaries-mali-west-africa-11661099199?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">雇佣了俄罗斯瓦格纳集团的雇佣兵</a>，而布基纳法索今年早些时候<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/burkina-faso-tells-french-troops-to-leave-11674503354?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">驱逐了法国军队</a>。萨赫勒东部的苏丹卷入了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sudan-khartoum-military-what-is-happening-447d40e2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">一场残酷的内战</a>，其中交战方之一也与瓦格纳合作。</p><p>这些联盟使尼日尔和巴祖姆成为西方在西非反恐行动的核心。美国在尼日尔驻有约 1,100 名士兵，而法国则在其前殖民地驻有约 1,500 名士兵以及无人机和喷气式战斗机。在马里邀请瓦格纳并驱逐法国人后，许多法国军队从马里转移到尼日尔。</p><p>周六，关于谁在管理这个国家的问题仍然存在。周五，尼日尔总统卫队司令阿卜杜拉哈马内·蒂亚尼将军表示，他所领导的军政府推翻了巴祖姆。他将该国反恐努力的挫折作为叛乱的原因。但周五，熟悉尼日尔局势的人士表示，废黜巴祖姆的陆军将领仍在争论谁最终将掌权。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——伊斯坦布尔的 Benoit Faucon 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 Vivian Salama（ <a href="mailto:vivian.salama@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">vivian.salama@wsj.com）</a>和 Gabriele Steinhauser（ <a href="mailto:Gabriele.Steinhauser@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Gabriele.Steinhauser@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 29 Jul 2023 13:42:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/blinken-says-us-aid-to-niger-in-jeopardy-following-coup-766a0156</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/blinken-says-us-aid-to-niger-in-jeopardy-following-coup-766a0156<author><![CDATA[Vivian SalamaGabriele Steinhauser]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>叛乱</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>恐怖主义</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>叛乱</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>恐怖主义</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Iran Renews Crackdown on Women Who Defy Islamic Dress Code]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>当局恢复街道巡逻并关闭员工藐视头巾规定的企业<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823081/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="越来越多的伊朗人违反了着装规定，该规定要求女性用头巾遮住头发。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>越来越多的伊朗人违反了着装规定，该规定要求女性用头巾遮住头发。 <span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001086931"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001086931"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sune-engel-rasmussen" itemprop="url" rel="author">Sune Engel Rasmussen</a></span> | Maryam Rahmanian 为《华尔街日报》拍摄的照片</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 29 日上午 7:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-renews-crackdown-on-women-who-defy-islamic-dress-code-a805794b"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>伊朗当局再次打击违反<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-makes-fresh-push-to-force-women-to-wear-hijab-7fefba6e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">该国严格着装规定的</a>女性，试图在去年因要求伊朗获得更多自由而引发的重大抗议活动后重新控制局势。</p><p>本周，当局关闭了该国领先的电子商务企业 Digikala（俗称伊朗亚马逊）的一个办公室，因为社交媒体上看到该公司的女员工没有戴头巾。他们还恢复了广受诟病的街头巡逻，以执行该国的伊斯兰着装规定，并关闭了数百家员工被发现违反规定的咖啡馆、餐馆和游乐园。</p><p>最近，警方关闭了一家新开张的美发沙龙，原因是一段女性在开业庆典上不戴面纱的视频在网上疯传， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-plans-penalties-for-women-breaking-hijab-rule-11673865037?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对违规行为的惩罚</a>也越来越多地旨在吸引公众的关注。</p><p>本月，一名妇女在首都德黑兰以南的一座城市开车时不戴头巾被发现，被法院判处一个月的清洗和准备尸体埋葬的刑罚。另一名妇女因涉嫌藐视头巾法而被判处 270 小时清洁政府大楼。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823119?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">伊朗的女性服装现在受到街头巡逻警察的仔细检查。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="846" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823113?width=1260&amp;height=846" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">着装规范要求女性穿着宽松的衣服遮盖自己的身体。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>伊朗警方本月表示，警察将恢复街头巡逻以遵守着装规定，伊朗人面临新的压力，该规定要求女性用头巾遮住头发，并穿着宽松的衣服遮住身体。男人因穿短裤而被骂。</p><p>尽管受到严厉打击，越来越多的女性公然违反着装规范。在德黑兰，妇女们穿着紧身牛仔裤，戴着宽松的头巾，露出辫子或亮点，坐着吃法式糕点。妇女们骑着摩托车和轻便摩托车在城里转悠，炫耀纹身，这也被认为是非伊斯兰教的，因为她们的头发在风中飘扬。</p><p>对于伊朗女性来说，骑摩托车并不违法，但实际上，当局很少向女性颁发骑摩托车许可证。然而，一些女司机表示，公众对女性交通的看法已经改变。</p><p> “五年前，骑摩托车的女人是一件大事。汽车不肯让路。即使是公共汽车也会挡住我的路，”33 岁的画家雷哈内 (Reyhaneh) 说，多年来她一直开着她的摩托车走遍首都各地。 “很多人会口头骚扰、嘲笑，甚至一度推我，”她说。 “但今天，文化已经改变了。”</p><p>她说，她从小就喜欢摩托车，但在一个保守的宗教家庭长大，她花了很多年才说服父亲让她拥有自己的轮子，即使只是一辆踏板车。</p><p> “我是家里的女儿，常常逆流而上，”雷哈内说。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-protesters-seek-end-of-an-islamic-republic-pillarthe-morality-police-11664383353?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">抗议活动</a>发生几个月后，该国的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-abolishes-morality-police-considers-changing-hijab-laws-official-says-11670165171?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">道德警察部队被解散</a>。抗议活动是在一名年轻女子<a href="https://www.wsj.com/story/who-is-mahsa-amini-and-why-did-her-death-spark-protests-in-iran-d4236eb3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">马萨·阿米尼因涉嫌衣着不雅而被警察逮捕后死亡而</a>引发的。</p><p>从那时起，正规警察越来越多地承担了以前由道德警察处理的任务。警方发言人在宣布恢复街头巡逻时表示，被发现违反着装规定的人将首先受到警告，如果不遵守则将被起诉。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823155?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">警方表示，任何违反着装规定的人都会首先受到警告，如果不遵守就会被起诉。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823154?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">强制戴头巾的批评者表示，它让一半的人在外出时感到压抑。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>四十多年来，头巾在伊朗一直是强制性的，并且备受争议。拥护它是教士领导捍卫伊斯兰教和国家基本原则的象征。</p><p>头巾也是一种政治控制工具，批评者称，它在外出时压迫了一半的人口。政府对着装规范的暴力执行是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-iran-protests-the-hijab-is-the-red-line-for-both-government-and-women-11666956847?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">去年大规模抗议活动</a>的导火索，这场抗议活动很快就从针对专制镇压服装的示威演变成对伊斯兰共和国生存的挑战。</p><p>在社交媒体上最近流传的一段视频中，一名未戴口罩的女子向路人尖叫着帮助她，却被一名身穿黑色长斗篷（罩袍）的女警官拉进了一辆货车。官方媒体称这段视频以及其他显示警察站在道德警察使用的类似货车前的视频是假的。报告称，由所谓的伊斯兰革命委员会监督的道德警察不会重返街头。</p><p>当局也在德黑兰以外地区进行镇压。据半官方的塔斯尼姆通讯社报道，在伊朗第二大城市马什哈德的宗教中心，他们根据当地头巾委员会的命令关闭了一座通往购物中心的人行天桥以及该建筑群中的几家咖啡馆。</p><p>德黑兰市中心时尚区一家咖啡馆的老板表示，多年来他因多种原因被迫关门，其中包括播放西方音乐，但人们的行为现在已经发生了不可逆转的改变。</p><p> “今天，人们来到这里，盛装打扮，就好像他们要去参加一个聚会一样，”他说。在去年的抗议活动中，他的咖啡馆和其他类似的咖啡馆成为抗议者的避难所，其中包括一些在与安全部队的冲突中受伤的人。咖啡馆老板说，几个月后，安全部队开始关闭商店。</p><p> Digikala 是一个拥有约 25 万卖家、拥有近 9,000 名员工的电子商务平台，对它的打击表明伊朗当局愿意针对私营企业，以维护许多伊朗人认为过时的社会习俗。尽管 Digikala 网站仍在运行，但该事件显示了私营企业的脆弱性，同时国际制裁加剧了伊朗的经济困难，并增加了此类企业蓬勃发展的需求。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823104?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">伊朗的一些观察家表示，尽管国家努力捍卫其基本原则，但人们的行为已经发生了变化。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823103?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">如今，在德黑兰的摩托车上，头发随风飘扬的女性已成为常见的景象。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>制裁使伊朗与全球经济的某些部分隔绝，包括亚马逊等电子商务网站。 Digikala 是伊朗初创企业领域的主要竞争对手，多年来一直是该国停滞经济中最有前途的增长替代方案之一，该国经济由国有石油和天然气生产和制造业主导，容易受到制裁和全球价格波动的影响。</p><p>围绕头巾的斗争加剧了伊斯兰共和国的其他困境，包括水资源短缺，特别是在该国动荡的东南部地区。</p><p>德黑兰咖啡馆老板表示，作为对私营企业监控的一部分，政府使用 Instagram 来识别违反伊斯兰着装规范的场所。他说，关闭 10 天会让他的企业损失约 10,000 美元。</p><p> “这不是钱的问题。这是他们给企业投下的恐惧阴影。”他补充说，关闭影响了一条漫长的供应链，从食品供应商和司机到他自己的 60 至 70 名员工。</p><p> “这个国家对待我这样的企业家的方式让我心碎，”他在他为咖啡馆翻修的旧三层建筑外说道。 “我把一栋破旧的房子变成了年轻人对话、文化交流、玩乐的场所。在世界其他任何地方，这都是值得赞赏的。”</p><p> <em>—Aresu Eqbali 对本文做出了贡献。</em></p><p>写信给 Sune Engel Rasmussen： <a href="mailto:sune.rasmussen@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">sune.rasmussen@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 29 Jul 2023 11:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-renews-crackdown-on-women-who-defy-islamic-dress-code-a805794b</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-renews-crackdown-on-women-who-defy-islamic-dress-code-a805794b<author><![CDATA[Sune Engel Rasmussen]]></author><category>电子商务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>容量/设施</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>设施关闭</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>容量</category><category>设施</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>设施关闭</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电子商务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[That Cool New Bookstore? It’s a Barnes & Noble.]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>美国最大的连锁书店正在重塑。要了解其 596 家商店的战略，请看最著名的一家。 <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823269/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="巴诺书店 (Barnes &amp; Noble) 首席执行官詹姆斯·道特 (James Daunt) 将改造后的上西区店视为其他商店的典范。 “如果我们能在这里做到的话，”他说。 “我们可以在任何地方做到这一点。”" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>巴诺书店 (Barnes &amp; Noble) 首席执行官詹姆斯·道特 (James Daunt) 将改造后的上西区店视为其他商店的典范。 “如果我们能在这里做到的话，”他说。 “我们可以在任何地方做。” <span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001090682"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001090682"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ben-cohen"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-555630/ba" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ben-cohen" itemprop="url" rel="author">本·科恩</a></span>克里斯托弗·格雷戈里-里维拉为《华尔街日报》拍摄的照片</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 29 日上午 12:01（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/barnes-noble-bookstores-james-daunt-c1afc06b"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>纽约——巴诺书店曾经是独立书店的敌人。现在它正努力变得更像他们。曼哈顿上西区的巴诺书店 (Barnes &amp; Noble) 更能诠释美国最大连锁书店的不可思议的重塑。</p><p>这家位于世界上最大的图书市场之一的商店自三十年前开业以来一直是一个战场。它可能是该连锁店 596 家门店中最具标志性的一家：正是这家商店为汤姆·汉克斯 (Tom Hanks) 在经典浪漫喜剧《电子情书》中饰演的角色经营的大型商店提供了灵感。</p><p>去年的大部分时间里，这里一直是一项大型实验的场所。该连锁店投资数百万美元将巴诺书店重建为其他商店效仿的典范，同时公司转型为现代书店。</p><p> “你不想在 Barnes &amp; Noble 里太疯狂，因为这家商店的乐趣之一就是每个人都来到这里，”自 2019 年该公司私有化以来的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/british-bookseller-plots-turnaround-at-barnes-noble-11565258401?mod=searchresults&amp;page=1&amp;pos=2&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">首席执行官</a>詹姆斯·道特 (James Daunt) 说道。我认为这会是一家非常有趣的书店，比现在有趣得多吗？哦，天哪，是的。”</p><p>他会知道的。在发现自己在英国和美国经营连锁书店之前，道特是伦敦一位受人尊敬的独立书商。他正是那种能让巴诺书店变得有趣的人。</p><p>他<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/barnes-nobles-new-boss-tries-to-save-the-chainand-traditional-bookselling-11607144485?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">拯救公司及其书店的计划</a>是将大型连锁店的力量与深受喜爱的独立书店的乐趣结合起来。通过将流程控制权转移给全国各地的个别商店经理，Daunt 允许当地书商做他们以前从未做过的事情。他们对购买、安置甚至定价都有自由裁量权。他希望 Barnes &amp; Noble 的店面给人一种受欢迎的感觉，但又不会让人感到压倒性的感觉——连锁店应该比真正的独立商店更有吸引力、更不那么令人生畏——这意味着他需要经营这些店的人为他们的市场做出明智的决定。 “如果它不有趣，那才是不可原谅的，”他说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="945" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823267?width=1260&amp;height=945" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">收银机和杂志已从上西区 Barnes &amp; Noble 的前面移开，以便为更多书籍让路。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>去年冬天他第一次带我参观上西区的巴诺书店时，语无伦次。外面又冷又沉闷，他在里面也有同样的感觉，他正试图理解各种各样奇怪的书籍。维奥拉·戴维斯的回忆录紧挨着弗朗茨·卡夫卡的日记。贾德·阿帕托的喜剧采访紧邻乔治·H·W·布什的精神传记。约翰·勒卡雷距离吉娜·戴维斯只有几英寸远。</p><p>我以为道特可能会把书从书架上拿出来，自己重新整理，但他的做法的要点是，首席执行官不应该是做出这些决定的人。书店的存在是为了服务读者，而不是出版商，不是投资者，更不是巴诺书店的老板。</p><p> Barnes &amp; Noble 在 20 世纪 90 年代和 2000 年代利用规模和统一性获得了好处，但这些优势后来变成了负担。各个书店不必都一样。他们也不应该这样。最好的管理者了解他们销售的书籍和购买这些书籍的顾客，而在上西区有效的方法可能不适用于西得梅因。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825378?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>新 Barnes &amp; Noble 背后的理念是让全国连锁店更像 596 家当地独立店的集合。我家附近的那个著名的曾经象征着公司的过去。现在它可以让我们一睹它的未来。 “如果我们能在这里做到，”当特说，“我们就可以在任何地方做到。”</p><p> Daunt 同意带我参观上西区改造项目的前后情况，所以我们在一月份见面，并计划在商店准备好后返回。当我们六月再次见面时，他所描述的愿景已经成为现实。</p><p>这次重大改造是必要的，因为自 1993 年这家书店开业以来，书店的使命已经发生了变化。当时，想要一本特定书籍的人会去他们最喜欢的实体店。现在任何需要这本书的人都可能访问亚马逊。</p><p>消费者行为的这种深刻转变促使巴诺书店重新考虑巴诺书店的宗旨。</p><p>一家实体书店要与价值 1.4 万亿美元的在线一切商店竞争，必须为人们提供他们知道自己想要的东西<em>和</em>他们不知道自己想要的东西。</p><p> “我们来这里是为了帮助人们浏览，”当特说。</p><p>但首先，上西区的位置必须是人们愿意花时间浏览的地方。暗淡的地砖被撕掉，换上了光滑的浅色木材。矮胖的森林绿色的单调地毯被不那么90年代的风格所取代。重新粉刷过的墙壁因粉红色的点缀而变得温暖起来。这个空间被设计得更加舒适和明亮，让您可以四处闲逛。</p><p>从您踏入酒店的那一刻起，最重要的变化就显而易见了。商店前面的收银机被推到了后面。这些杂志莫名其妙地占据了一楼的黄金地段，被塞在楼上搬迁的咖啡馆旁边。它们必须被移动，以便为更多的书籍腾出空间。</p><p>还有很多书。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="945" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823270?width=1260&amp;height=945" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">对于书籍的展示方式，道特有自己的想法，但他希望当地管理者拥有最终权力。 “如果它不有趣，那才是不可原谅的，”他说。</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>你有一家新书店</h3><p>詹姆斯·道特 (James Daunt) 在成为巴诺书店 (Barnes &amp; Noble) 首席执行官时就已经有了一份工作。事实上，他有两个。</p><p>他于 1990 年开始涉足这一行业，当时他创立了伦敦独立出版社 Daunt Books，以其无可挑剔的品味而闻名。他那家精美的精品店最终发展成为由遍布英格兰的九家商店组成的集团，至今仍由他负责管理。然后，他出人意料地出任 Waterstones（英国的 Barnes &amp; Noble）最高职位。2011 年，他继承了一家拥有大约 300 家门店、陷入困境的连锁店，之后，他将这家公司从亏损的资金中<a href="https://charts.dowjones.io/wsj/chart/bbf05182e4a92bdbad6f6cc3" target="_blank" class="icon none">扭亏为盈</a>。 Waterstones <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elliott-management-buys-british-bookstore-chain-waterstones-1524762100?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">于 2018 年被激进对冲基金 Elliott Management 收购</a>，该基金让 Daunt 继续掌管，并将目标瞄准了 Barnes &amp; Noble 本身。</p><p>这家管理不善的连锁店在首席执行官更换之后，甚至在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/BL-DLB-32313" target="_blank" class="icon none">其竞争对手鲍德斯（Borders）</a>倒闭后也损失了一半的年收入，因此收购的时机已经成熟。埃利奥特<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/barnes-noble-to-be-acquired-by-elliott-management-for-6-50-a-share-11559906841" target="_blank" class="icon none">在这笔交易中支付了 4.75 亿美元</a>，并任命道特领导另一次不太可能的东山再起。</p><p> 59 岁的道特说话轻声细语，就像在图书馆里一样，但他的管理哲学核心洞察力值得在屋顶上尖叫：找到对书籍充满热情的人，让他们以自己认为合适的方式出售书籍。当他这么说时，这听起来相当明显。但将一家连锁店委托给不久前在伦敦市中心经营一家豪华商店的人是企业绝望的激进行为。</p><p>当我们在上西区的巴诺书店漫步时，当特说：“我认为它几乎已经死了，才会有人愿意冒这个险。” “水石死后我接管了它，而它几乎没有呼吸时我接管了这个地方，这绝非巧合。”</p><p>衡量书店健康状况的一种方法是退货率，即零售商退回给出版商的未售出图书的百分比。越低越好。</p><p>当他开始工作时，Waterstones 和 Barnes &amp; Noble 的退货率都在 20% 到 25% 之间。 Waterstones 的折扣降至 3.5%。 Daunt 说，Barnes &amp; Noble&#39;s 的比例是 9%。他的目标是5%。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="1008" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825690?width=1260&amp;height=1008" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在改建后的巴诺书店，一排排的书变成了书房。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="945" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825720?width=1260&amp;height=945" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">显示表的组织方式巧妙，超越了算法建议。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>并不是所有人都对他让巴诺书店成为一家更有效率的企业的计划感到兴奋，出版商担心这将导致美国最大的连锁店购买更少的图书。各个商店的经理对他们的库存和定价方式有更多的控制权，这意味着出版商的库存会减少。出版界的其他人对本土品味在日益受到全国畅销书推动的行业中的重要性表示怀疑。</p><p>在美国书店销售触底之前，Daunt 被 Barnes &amp; Noble 聘用。根据联邦数据，从 2008 年到 2019 年，这些数字每年都在下降，并在 2020 年陷入困境。但事实证明，自疫情爆发第一年以来，零售商表现出惊人的韧性。销售额在 2021 年反弹。2022 年继续上升。2023 年销售额有望再次增长。</p><p>作为一家私营公司，巴诺书店不报告财务业绩，但很明显它不再濒临死亡。虽然自收购以来门店数量减少了 5%，但该连锁店目前正在扩张，并计划今年开设 45 家门店，其中包括一些关闭后重新开业但占地面积较小的门店，例如本月在上东区开业的一家门店围绕街区排线。它还对全国各地的现有商店进行了改造。但并不是每家商店都需要彻底改造才能焕然一新。最近，我走进了科罗拉多州普韦布洛州际公路旁的一家 Barnes &amp; Noble 商店，那里即使是细微的调整也会带来令人愉悦的浏览体验。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="928" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/73ca436e-4e09-46ee-a0fa-2a8f88d0efba-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Daunt 选择以 400 万美元的翻新费来挽救上西区的商店，与开设一家这种规模的新商店的成本相同，因为他觉得建筑本身很漂亮，而且百老汇的位置很理想。他还认为，这家连锁店需要在曼哈顿这片书卷气十足的地区拥有强大的影响力。他来自伦敦，那里有几十家 Waterstones 门店，但他沮丧地发现，在他这个“极其没有书店”的新城市里，只有 7 家 Barnes &amp; Nobles 书店。</p><p> “这并不是因为纽约人不买书，”他说。 “那是因为书店倒闭了。”</p><p>就连电影里的书店也无法继续营业。在 1998 年的浪漫喜剧《情有可原》中，汤姆·汉克斯和梅格·瑞恩扮演竞争对手上西区书商乔·福克斯和凯瑟琳·凯利，当他的 Fox &amp; Sons 连锁书店在街上开业时，她关闭了街角商店并承诺“廉价书籍和合法的、令人上瘾的兴奋剂”。</p><p>这部电影部分取材于巴诺书店入侵社区以及随之而来的现实生活戏剧。在《电子情书》上映时，该公司的市值比亚马逊还要高，但那是 25 年前的事了，价值数万亿美元。既然<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/WMT" class="company-name">亚马逊</a>如此之大，以至于沃尔玛看起来很小，那么将一家设有浓缩咖啡吧的书店视为邪恶的企业恶霸是很奇怪的。</p><p>如今，每家书店都是街角商店，甚至是福克斯图书超市。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825381?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>当然，今天的纽约也有蓬勃发展的真正独立音乐人、像 McNally Jackson 和 Books Are Magic 这样的精致商店，以及像 The Strand 这样拥有忠实顾客的机构。他们散发着难以言喻的魅力，几乎无法复制。</p><p> “独立书店总是给人一种独特的、由业主经营的感觉，这是连锁店所没有的，”纽约莎士比亚书店首席执行官戴恩·内勒 (Dane Neller) 说。 “你只是不是。”</p><p>道特碰巧同意了。作为一个能与乔·福克斯和凯瑟琳·凯利产生共鸣的人，他具有独特的资格来比较独立游戏和连锁游戏，尽管他承认直到我们见面后才看过《电子情书》。他告诉我 Daunt Books 与 Barnes &amp; Noble 完全不同，而且两者都有一席之地。 “像这样的大商店总是会多得多、少得多，”他说。但仅仅因为它不一样并不意味着它不能相似。 “在连锁店里，”他说，“你可以创造出很多独立书店的精神。”</p><p>业务战略并不是 Barnes &amp; Noble 在 Daunt 领导下不断发展的唯一部分。这也是每个书店的目标。</p><p> “进来享受一下吧，”他说。 “与目前有效的<em>存在理由</em>相反，即以一种你可以找到的方式将这些书堆起来，然后你找到你想要的书并离开。这是一个重大的旧转变。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="474" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825169?width=700&amp;height=474" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在 1998 年的《电子情书》中，汤姆·汉克斯 (Tom Hanks) 饰演一位经营巴诺书店 (Barnes &amp; Noble) 连锁店的高管。梅格·瑞恩扮演一个被汉克斯赶出生意的独立竞争对手。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：华纳兄弟/埃弗雷特收藏</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>“我没有意识到我有多无聊”</h3><p>今年夏天的一天，道特被难住了。他正在谈论指导巴诺书店员工将每本书放在每个书架上的位置的设备，但不记得它的名字。他向一名在上西区商店整理精装小说的年轻员工寻求帮助。 She told him it was called a PDT—a portable data terminal. Then she explained that the store&#39;s 30 booksellers weren&#39;t really working with PDTs anymore. They were using their brains instead of following the <em>beep-beep-beep</em> of a scanner. He thanked her and walked away.</p><p> “She has no idea who I am,” Daunt whispered.</p><p> The CEO of Barnes &amp; Noble was standing in the front of a busy store that was completely unrecognizable from six months earlier.</p><p> He was surrounded by books.</p><p> There were 87,756 in stock on a recent day, including 2,000 titles on the ground floor alone, which Daunt estimated to be “a ton more” than before. There were piles of bestselling fiction, nonfiction and mysteries. There were popular cookbooks and children&#39;s books hugging the columns where shoppers naturally gravitate. There was an upstairs level that stretched across the building on a full city block. And there was still an entire wall of bare shelves waiting to be lined. “We need <em>more</em> books,” said Victoria Harty, the assistant store manager.</p><p> But swarming Barnes &amp; Noble shoppers with books wasn&#39;t enough. The books themselves also had to be optimized for discovery. Many covers face outward instead of spines. Handwritten staff picks float off shelves. Neatly curated tables are organized in clever ways that transcend algorithmic recommendations.</p><p> It had been grueling to keep the store open during construction, but the booksellers could see the results of that work in this humming store, even if it wasn&#39;t nearly done yet. “There&#39;s a thousand little things that need doing,” said Jason Byrnes, the store&#39;s manager. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="1276" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825728?width=1260&amp;height=1276" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Assistant Manager Victoria Harty and Manager Jason Byrnes at the Upper West Side Barnes &amp; Noble.</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Byrnes went to elementary school in the neighborhood, so this was his childhood bookstore long before it was his office. After working in other Barnes &amp; Nobles around Manhattan and Brooklyn, he was recruited back to the one where he grew up. Daunt said the store&#39;s former manager oversaw the initial phase of the construction so well that he moved her into a new role handling those projects elsewhere. To fill the vacancy, he looked for talented booksellers with local knowledge and skills that would fit well together, and he found people like Harty and Byrnes. It turned out having the authority to make their own decisions was more stimulating, gratifying and way more fun than taking orders from a machine.</p><p> “I didn&#39;t realize how bored I was,” Byrnes said.</p><p> To run hundreds of stores the way he runs the one with his name, Daunt needs to recruit more full-time employees and pay them to stick around. They won&#39;t become model booksellers overnight. Many won&#39;t be booksellers forever. But most can grow to be great at one part of the job and show their peers at nearby stores how they do it. The person studying data to order books at one Barnes &amp; Noble in Atlanta can train inventory specialists at other stores in the area more effectively than an executive from corporate headquarters. It&#39;s a brilliant formula when it works: Daunt likes to say that the less he does, the smarter he looks. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=DDFEDF5F-C702-4D6A-9EE9-EE3FF6AE1A8A&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fbarnes-noble-bookstores-james-daunt-c1afc06b&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Barnes &amp; Noble grew into a bookselling powerhouse thanks in part to the rapid expansion of its cookie-cutter retail locations. After years of struggling against e-commerce, it&#39;s adopted a local strategy, empowering individual stores to decide on inventory and displays. Photo illustration: Ryan Trefes<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>But to look around a Barnes &amp; Noble with him is to see the questions worth thinking about in every nook of the bookstore. What is the optimal table density? Does “Life” by Keith Richards belong with other memoirs or music books about the Rolling Stones? How should the history section be arranged?</p><p> There&#39;s not always a right answer. But there are wrong answers. It baffles Daunt that 20% of the chain&#39;s locations sort history books alphabetically by author. “This was a store that had history arranged A-to-Z,” he said last month. “Now it&#39;s chronological.”</p><p> A bookstore should be intuitive enough for a child to navigate but compelling enough that adults don&#39;t mind getting lost. Because this one has an eccentric layout over 28,000 square feet—books on two floors, gifts and toys on the mezzanine—Byrnes and his team made it a priority to improve the flow. They reconfigured the map based on customer feedback. On the upstairs level, where toddlers run around and teens flirt after school, they moved entire sections around. “Then moved them again and moved them again,” he said. Rows of books became rooms of books. Displays on the side of bookcases were treated like vertical tables. Shelves grew two rows taller to “reclaim the air” without reducing inventory, Daunt said. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825382?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> There were another thousand little things that still needed to be done—and those small details would turn into something much bigger. Daunt has learned from his decades of experience that there is a direct correlation between how a bookstore looks and how it performs.</p><p> “It&#39;s really peculiar if good bookstores don&#39;t sell more books,” he said. “They always do in the end.”</p><p> The real question is how many more. Daunt expects this Barnes &amp; Noble&#39;s sales to double from their 2019 levels by 2026.</p><p> But the remodeled store is already seeing a sales uptick because of the shrewd decisions of its booksellers. By the front door is a table of literary historical fiction that includes “The Weight of Ink” by Rachel Kadish and “People of the Book” by Geraldine Brooks, paperbacks that had been hiding upstairs because they were published several years ago. Harty moved them downstairs. She knew they would interest highbrow Jewish readers on the Upper West Side more than the median shopper in the average market. She was right. They went from selling one copy a month to 20.</p><p> “One of the first things we did when we first got here was to start building the tables,” Byrnes said. “To watch the titles we brought in consistently show up as our top-selling books was very satisfying.”</p><p> Daunt and I were standing by that table last month when a shopper walked past us with a Daunt Books tote bag—the ultimate sign that something unexpected is happening at Barnes &amp; Noble.</p><p> “We&#39;re giving them what I think they recognize as a really good bookstore,” Daunt said.</p><p> But I was curious for one more opinion of the Barnes &amp; Noble on the Upper West Side. So a few weeks ago, I emailed Joe Fox himself: Tom Hanks.</p><p> As it happens, Hollywood&#39;s most famous bibliophile recently published his first novel, which is featured on its own table in this chain bookstore that&#39;s beginning to feel like an indie.</p><p> “I&#39;ve never been in the newly transformed B&amp;N,” Hanks wrote, “but I approve the concept.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="945" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823273?width=1260&amp;height=945" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> There were 87,756 titles in stock on a recent day at the Upper West Side Barnes &amp; Noble.</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Write to Ben Cohen at <a href="mailto:ben.cohen@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ben.cohen@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 29 Jul 2023 04:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/barnes-noble-bookstores-james-daunt-c1afc06b</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/barnes-noble-bookstores-james-daunt-c1afc06b<author><![CDATA[Ben Cohen]]></author><category>摄影委托</category><category>世杰交易所</category><category>exchangecover</category><category>零售批发</category><category>Book/Office Supplies Retailing</category><category> Book Retailing</category><category>专业零售</category><category>零售</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>名人</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> James Daunt</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>celebrities</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>零售</category><category>批发的</category><category>书</category><category>office supplies retailing</category><category> book retailing</category><category>专业零售</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia Uses Little-Known Traders to Sell Oil to the World]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> The success of Rosneft&#39;s recent oil tender adds to signs that the financial squeeze on Russian oil producers from sanctions is abating <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001093385"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="581" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825822?width=860&amp;height=581" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> State-controlled Rosneft wrapped up one of its biggest oil tenders in years.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Sergei Karpukhin/REUTERS </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001093385"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/anna-hirtenstein" itemprop="url" rel="author">Anna Hirtenstein</a></span> , <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/costas-paris" itemprop="url" rel="author">Costas Paris</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/joe-wallace" itemprop="url" rel="author">Joe Wallace</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 28, 2023 1:56 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-uses-little-known-traders-to-sell-oil-to-the-world-4bb538cd"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Russia struck deals to sell a substantial portion of its petroleum output to a group of previously little-known oil traders, locking in a stream of cash from its lifeblood industry.</p><p> State-controlled energy giant Rosneft Oil in recent weeks wrapped up <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-nears-deals-to-sell-gusher-of-oil-b0483a83?mod=Searchresults_pos1&amp;page=1&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">one of its largest tenders in years</a> , people familiar with the sale said. A tender is a type of auction in which traders bid for the right to export oil in the future. In this case, the contracts are for up to 12 months and involve crude and refined products, some of the people said.</p><p> It couldn&#39;t be learned the exact amounts of oil sold, nor the prices. But the success of the tender—a similar effort last year failed—adds to signs that the financial squeeze on Russian oil producers from sanctions is abating. The price of Russia&#39;s main variety of crude <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-defies-sanctions-by-selling-oil-above-price-cap-bae1c271?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">has risen above a Western-imposed cap</a> in recent weeks.</p><p> A Rosneft spokesperson said that the company doesn&#39;t comment on the details of its business activities and that some of what was presented in a series of questions about the tender was incorrect. When asked which details were inaccurate, the spokesperson didn&#39;t reply.</p><p> The results cement the role of a clutch of upstart trading houses as vehicles for Russian oil to reach new markets. These companies <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/little-known-commodity-traders-help-russia-sell-oil-11653643583?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">rose to prominence</a> after Russia&#39;s invasion of Ukraine, filling a hole left when the world&#39;s largest commodities merchants—such as Trafigura Group, Vitol and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GLNCY" class="company-name">Glencore</a> —pulled back from Russia.</p><p> Among the biggest winners in the tender was Bellatrix Energy, the people familiar with the sale said. According to registration documents, the company was incorporated in Hong Kong. Also taking large volumes of Russian petroleum were trading group Amur and Tejarinaft, both registered in the United Arab Emirates.</p><p> All three have been active exporters of crude and refined products since sanctions on Russian oil took effect in December, according to Russian customs data and industry executives.</p><p> Bellatrix didn&#39;t respond to requests for comment. Representatives for Amur entities involved in oil trading in the UAE couldn&#39;t be reached to comment. A representative for Amur entities in Switzerland declined to comment. Emails sent to an address listed on Tejarinaft&#39;s website bounced back. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="445" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825837?width=700&amp;height=445" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Crude-oil tankers anchoring near the port city of Nakhodka, Russia, in December.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: TATIANA MEEL/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The traders perform a vital role for Rosneft and other Russian producers, handling the complex logistics needed to move millions of barrels of petroleum daily to overseas buyers. They have, according to shipping records and the industry executives, worked closely with other upstart firms, based in the UAE and India, that have amassed <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/upstart-indian-shipper-helps-get-russian-oil-to-market-11674985846?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">control of hundreds of old tankers</a> used to move Russian oil.</p><p> Trading, shipping and refining Russian oil became a lucrative business in the wake of the Ukraine invasion in February 2022. The price dropped to steep discounts to global benchmarks—discounts that remain wide by prewar standards even after narrowing in recent months. Western governments monitor oil flows to gauge whether sanctions have succeeded in hurting Russia&#39;s wartime economy, and to spot any violations.</p><p> The US, Europe and other backers of Kyiv targeted Russian energy in several rounds of sanctions. They designed the measures to ensure a continued flow of Russian oil onto world markets so as not to drive up gasoline prices, but also to throw sand in the gears of Russia&#39;s export logistics and limit how much Moscow can earn from each barrel it sells.</p><p> Russia&#39;s favored trading and shipping players have little public profile. That makes it hard to determine how money flows through the oil market and whether it works its way back to the Russian budget. The paper trail left in publicly available documents doesn&#39;t fully show who ultimately controls them and backs them financially, according to industry executives.</p><p> Amur and Tejarinaft entities based in the UAE share the same managing director, Hicham Fizazi, a Moroccan national, Emirati corporate records show. An engineer by training, Fizazi previously traded wheat and invested in affordable housing, according to Tejarinaft&#39;s website. Fizazi was named as chairman of an Amur holding company in Geneva in minutes of a shareholders&#39; meeting reviewed by The Wall Street Journal dated December last year. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825841?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A Rosneft gas station in St. Petersburg.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Maksim Konstantinov/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Fizazi couldn&#39;t be reached to comment.</p><p> The Geneva company was set up in 2021 by trading giant Vitol and midsize merchant Mercantile &amp; Maritime Group. The joint venture traded Russian oil and invested in a major Russian development project known as Vostok Oil.</p><p> Vitol sold its stake in the Swiss Amur holding company to Emirati firm Fossil Trading FZCO after the invasion of Ukraine, a spokeswoman said. She added that Vitol has no stakes in Amur entities in the UAE</p><p> Mercantile &amp; Maritime sold its Vostok stake, according to the company&#39;s website. It divested from Amur Trading and Amur Investments in Switzerland and has no stakes in the UA E entities, a person familiar with the matter said.</p><p> Fossil Trading didn&#39;t respond to requests for comment.</p><p> Until recently, records showed that Tejarinaft&#39;s website registrant was Edward Ghazal, previously a commercial manager at Mercantile &amp; Maritime&#39;s Singapore office, according to his LinkedIn profile. In 2020, he was also a director at Myanmar Petroleum Services, which is majority owned by Mercantile &amp; Maritime, corporate filings showed. This week, the registrant changed to Fizazi.</p><p> Ghazal didn&#39;t respond to requests for comment.</p><p> Bellatrix&#39;s director is Ahmet Songan, a Turkish national. He couldn&#39;t be reached to comment.</p><p> Bellatrix has exported almost 25 million metric tons in crude and fuel this year from Rosneft and other Russian producers, including a subsidiary of state giant Gazprom, according to the customs data. In December, Bellatrix took out a loan facility with state-owned Russian Agricultural Bank of up to $350 million, to be repaid by mid-2025, according to a filing in Hong Kong.</p><p> Bellatrix borrowed from lenders including Russian Regional Development Bank, a subsidiary of Rosneft, a Hong Kong filing shows. As security, it pledged a contract for exporting oil products from India&#39;s Nayara Energy, which had been transferred to Bellatrix by UAE-based trader Coral Energy. Bellatrix also pledged a separate contract for selling oil products to Coral.</p><p> Russian Agricultural Bank and Russian Regional Development Bank are both sanctioned by the US</p><p> Representatives for Russian Agricultural Bank, Russian Regional Development Bank, Gazprom and Nayara didn&#39;t respond to requests for comment.</p><p> Another trader, Nord Axis, exported more than 50 million metric tons of crude and fuel this year through the end of May, according to Russian customs data. It was incorporated in Hong Kong nine days before the invasion of Ukraine.</p><p> Murat Sayin, founding partner of energy-focused Sayin Law &amp; Consulting in Turkey and Nord Axis&#39;s director, said that the contracts under which the company traded Russian oil had expired and that Nord Axis didn&#39;t participate in the recent tender. Nord Axis hasn&#39;t entered into any new contracts for Russian oil because of logistical complications and rising competition in the market, he said.</p><p> Write to Anna Hirtenstein at <a href="mailto:anna.hirtenstein@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">anna.hirtenstein@wsj.com</a> , Costas Paris at <a href="mailto:costas.paris@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">costas.paris@wsj.com</a> and Joe Wallace at <a href="mailto:joe.wallace@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">joe.wallace@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 17:56:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-uses-little-known-traders-to-sell-oil-to-the-world-4bb538cd</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-uses-little-known-traders-to-sell-oil-to-the-world-4bb538cd<author><![CDATA[Anna HirtensteinCostas ParisJoe Wallace]]></author><category>专有的</category><category>活力</category><category>化石燃料</category><category>Integrated Oil/Gas</category><category>油和气</category><category>Oil</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>Contracts/Orders</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>Trade/External Payments</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>Trade Barriers/Restrictions</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Rosneft Oil</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>合同</category><category>命令</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>贸易</category><category>external payments</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治</category><category>trade barriers</category><category>限制</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>活力</category><category>化石燃料</category><category>integrated oil</category><category>气体</category><category>油和气</category><category>oil </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Putin Pledges Free Grain Shipments for African Allies]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Governments across Africa are on edge after Russia ended a deal for the safe passage of Ukrainian grain <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001093964"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825853?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Russian President Vladimir Putin posed for a group photo with African heads of state and other delegates at the Russia-Africa summit in St. Petersburg, Russia, on Friday.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Mikhail tereschenko/tass/epa/Shutterstock </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001093964"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ann-m-simmons" itemprop="url" rel="author">Ann M. Simmons</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated July 28, 2023 1:52 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/putin-pledges-free-grain-shipments-for-african-allies-afa6a003"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Russian President <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin">Vladimir Putin</a> pledged to ship food and provide more security assistance to a swath of African nations after his move to end a deal <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/great-power-rivalry-looms-over-ukraine-grain-deal-3d2e0eb1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">safeguarding the export of Ukrainian grain</a> , rattling nerves in many of the continent&#39;s most vulnerable nations.</p><p> Putin is trying to maintain the support of several of Russia&#39;s Cold War-era partners, and on Friday, the final day of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-need-of-allies-putin-courts-african-leaders-in-st-petersburg-b6596a7b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a two-day summit</a> in St. Petersburg, Russia, he told African leaders that he was ready to train their militaries, write off debts and provide thousands of tons of wheat and corn. He also pledged to extend trade relationships with African nations, some of which already have close ties to Moscow, while offering to help modernize their own agricultural sectors and open new embassies.</p><p> “I would also like to note that before our very eyes, the African continent is becoming a new center of power,” Putin told his counterparts. “Its political and economic role is growing exponentially. And everyone will have to reckon with this objective reality.”</p><p> Africa—the largest regional grouping represented at the United Nations, with 54 governments—is becoming an influential element in <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraines-stalled-offensive-puts-biden-in-uneasy-political-position-6f686ab5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the tussle between Russia and Ukraine</a> for international support.</p><p> Many African nations have refrained from taking a position on the war in Ukraine, and the 17 heads of state who attended this week&#39;s forum—a drop from the more than 40 who attended the first such summit in 2019—remained noncommittal in public.</p><p> Putin later praised the African leaders who attended the event for having “shown political will, demonstrated their independence and real interest in developing cooperation” with Russia.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> The Russian leader denied that Moscow&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/why-russia-killed-the-ukraine-grain-deal-faf1f8c5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">withdrawal from the UN-brokered Black Sea grain initiative</a> —an agreement guaranteeing safe passage for Ukraine&#39;s vast wheat and corn exports—was responsible for destabilizing global food supplies. He has instead blamed the West&#39;s sanctions on Russia for hampering exports of fertilizers and other products, and accused the UN of failing to meet Moscow&#39;s requirements to extend the Black Sea deal.</p><p> Putin reiterated his pledge to provide 25,000 to 50,000 tons of grain to six African nations, free of charge, in the coming few months. He also noted that Russia had written off $23 billion in African debt and would allocate over $90 million more for these purposes and for development “at the latest requests from African countries,” he said.</p><p> There is widespread skepticism over the Kremlin&#39;s ability to make good on such promises at a time when Russia&#39;s economy is now constrained by Western sanctions and its military campaign in Ukraine.</p><p> In remarks at Friday&#39;s plenary session, Cyril Ramaphosa, president of the continent&#39;s powerhouse South Africa, said his country was “encouraged by the Russian Federation&#39;s commitment to deepening collaboration with the nations of Africa.” He said the continent was seeking “reciprocal trade and investment, and for the goods, products and services from Africa to compete on an equal footing in the global economy.”</p><p> While avoiding the appearance of being publicly critical of Putin, some African leaders didn&#39;t hold back on urging the Russian president to restore the grain deal and end Moscow&#39;s war in Ukraine.</p><p> “It&#39;s necessary to find an urgent and quick solution to the problems of food supplies to countries in need, while paying attention to all issues related to this topic,” Egyptian President Abdel Fattah Al Sisi, whose country is one of the world&#39;s top importers of wheat, told a plenary chaired by Putin, according to Russia&#39;s state news agency, TASS. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="475" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825854?width=700&amp;height=475" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Egyptian President Abdel Fattah Al Sisi was among African leaders who urged Putin to restore the Black Sea grain initiative and end the war in Ukraine.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Egyptian President Office/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Hit hard by the economic fallout from the conflict, a group of African leaders have <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/african-leaders-bring-peace-proposal-to-ukraine-as-kyiv-and-moscow-vie-for-support-f974a3bd?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">crafted a peace proposal</a> aimed at ending the hostilities and securing predictable food supplies. The plan has so far gained little traction with either Russia or Ukraine.</p><p> On Friday, Denis Sassou Nguesso, president of the Republic of the Congo, called for an end to the fighting in Ukraine. He told Putin and his African counterparts that the African peace initiative deserves close attention and “should not be underestimated,” TASS cited him as saying.</p><p> Ramaphosa, the South African leader, said it was his country&#39;s hope that “constructive engagement and negotiation” could bring an end to the conflict, according to comments published by his office.</p><p> Putin said that he would consider the African nations&#39; proposals, but said Ukraine needed to be convinced.</p><p> “We cannot impose these negotiations,” Putin said, adding that “it&#39;s necessary to conduct a dialogue with the other side, although we are grateful to our African friends for their attention to this problem.”</p><p> His comments came as the Russian military continued to bombard Ukraine&#39;s ports, which are a critical component in the global food supply chain.</p><p> Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky has said that any cease-fire that allows Russia to keep Ukrainian territories seized since the invasion last year would only encourage a wider conflict, giving Moscow an opportunity to replenish and rearm for another round of fighting.</p><p> Write to Ann M. Simmons at <a href="mailto:ann.simmons@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ann.simmons@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 17:52:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/putin-pledges-free-grain-shipments-for-african-allies-afa6a003</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/putin-pledges-free-grain-shipments-for-african-allies-afa6a003<author><![CDATA[Ann M. Simmons]]></author><category>乌克兰</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>Trade/External Payments</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>Trade Barriers/Restrictions</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Vladimir Putin</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>贸易</category><category>external payments</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>trade barriers</category><category>限制</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Europe Avoids China’s Belt and Road Forum, Keeping a Distance From Xi and Putin]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>俄罗斯总统确认出席计划中的峰会，阻止北京想要拉拢的西方国家<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001089733"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824151?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> “一带一路”倡议是中国领导人习近平的标志性经济外交平台。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Florence Lo/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001089733"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/chunhan-wong" itemprop="url" rel="author">Chun Han Wong</a></span> （新加坡）、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/laurence-norman" itemprop="url" rel="author">Laurence Norman</a></span> （柏林）和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/drew-hinshaw" itemprop="url" rel="author">Drew Hinshaw</a></span> （马德里）</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 28 日中午 12:19（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/europe-avoids-chinas-belt-and-road-forum-keeping-a-distance-from-xi-and-putin-14f6253b"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>经过三年的新冠隔离后，中国领导人习近平正计划对其标志性的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-belt-road-debt-11663961638?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">“一带一路”基础设施倡议</a>发起一场井喷式的攻击。</p><p>回复并没有完全到来。</p><p>尤其是欧洲国家，他们不参加庆祝活动，这反映出欧洲大陆与欧洲国家之间的关系恶化。 <strong>&nbsp;</strong>中国。北京曾希望欧洲能够融入其全球贸易和运输联系的“一带一路”网络，但欧洲领导人正在放弃，与华盛顿一样对增加对中国的经济依赖持谨慎态度。</p><p>一位自称将出席的重要嘉宾——俄罗斯总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin">弗拉基米尔·普京</a>——进一步赶走了欧洲领导人，其中许多人因乌克兰战争爆发以来北京对莫斯科的支持而对中国采取了强硬立场。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=D22F13F2-B14C-4B01-9BDA-B329319CAD58&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Feurope-avoids-chinas-belt-and-road-forum-keeping-a-distance-from-xi-and-putin-14f6253b&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> 《华尔街日报》的谢尔比·霍利迪 (Shelby Holliday) 解释了中国的“一带一路”倡议为何遭到破坏、“一带一路”2.0 可能是什么样子，以及此类改革可能给中国带来的挑战。插图：阿黛尔·摩根<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>北京设想的“一带一路”倡议将一些专家估计的1万亿美元用于中国资助的铁路、公路、管道和港口，这些项目将连接亚洲与欧洲、非洲和拉丁美洲。</p><p>就在五年前，中国迅速在发展中国家加入新成员，并通过“一带一路”资助的货物抵达欧洲港口和铁路，进军与华盛顿更紧密合作的富裕经济体，包括意大利、希腊和捷克共和国。 。</p><p>现在，随着欧洲寻求减少中国在该地区的经济影响力，其中许多国家正在远离该项目。</p><p>据政府高级官员透露，法国总统马克龙和德国总理肖尔茨目前没有计划参加今年的“一带一路”高峰论坛。一位协调其日程的人士表示，意大利总理乔治亚·梅洛尼（Giorgia Meloni）也是七国集团中唯一签署“一带一路”倡议的国家。瑞士外交部发言人表示，历史上保持中立的瑞士正在考虑是否参加今年的峰会，该国在过去的两次峰会上都派出了自己的总统。</p><p> 2018年加入“一带一路”倡议的希腊已经告诉北京，其总理不会参加。政府发言人表示，捷克共和国于 2015 年签署了该倡议，预计不会派出总统或高级官员。在这些国家承诺与北京开展“一带一路”合作后，习近平对这些国家进行了为期三天的国事访问。</p><p>欧盟委员会主席乌尔苏拉·冯德莱恩今年三月表示，北京对“一带一路”的追求是“中国共产党的明确目标是对以中国为中心的国际秩序进行系统性改变”的迹象之一。</p><p>习近平于 2013 年首次提出的“一带一路”倡议是一项促进全球发展和扩大中国国际影响力的广泛运动，是世界上最大的基础设施计划——比华盛顿战后的马歇尔计划规模大得多——而美国一直未能到目前为止，已经找到了替代方案。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="493" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824667?width=700&amp;height=493" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 2019 年在北京举行的上届“一带一路”高峰论坛上，各国元首合影留念。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：瓦列里·梅尔尼科夫/Sputnik/Shutterstock</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>但“一带一路”支出<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-global-mega-projects-infrastructure-falling-apart-11674166180?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">未达到早期预期</a>，而且北京的雄心因Covid-19、借贷成本上升和俄罗斯在乌克兰的战争而受到挫伤。今年的“一带一路”高峰论坛是疫情以来的第一届，也是自 2017 年首届以来的第三届，将考验习近平标志性经济外交平台的吸引力，中国外交官将努力填补嘉宾名单并展示中国的全球影响力。</p><p> “过去几年，欧洲国家以开放的态度对待‘一带一路’倡议，”荣鼎集团研究欧洲和中国问题的诺亚·巴尔金 (Noah Barkin) 表示。巴尔金表示，现在，人们的看法已经发生了转变，该计划在很大程度上被视为“中国在海外传播影响力的工具”。</p><p>迄今为止，欧洲的反应平淡表明，全球格局对习近平的外交野心来说更具挑战性。如果欧洲国家<strong>&nbsp;</strong>曾经考虑加入“一带一路”，现在却与之竞争。</p><p> 10月下旬，欧洲各国政府将邀请来自非洲、拉丁美洲和亚洲（但不包括中国）的商界领袖、官员和国家元首参加他们自己的竞争对手论坛，宣传欧盟耗资3330亿美元的基础设施建设计划“全球门户”。</p><p>与此同时，据知情人士透露，中国官员正在努力争取在 10 月中旬召开北京论坛，并一直在争取外国政府的参与。</p><h3> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/story/xi-and-putin-a-friendship-forged-against-the-west-866dfcf1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">习近平和普京：对抗西方的友谊</a></h3><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-interactiveLink"><div class="image-container"> <a class="interactive-link" href="https://www.wsj.com/story/xi-and-putin-a-friendship-forged-against-the-west-866dfcf1"><img width="16" height="10" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-748166?width=700&amp;height=463" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><span class="image-interactive-icon">
            </span></a></div><div class="wsj-article-caption"><span class="wsj-article-credit">帕维尔·伯金/人造卫星/克里姆林宫</span></div></div></div><p>官方媒体此前曾报道，习近平在三月份对莫斯科进行国事访问期间邀请普京出席。本周，克里姆林宫表示普京将参加。</p><p>知情人士称，普京的出现使得中国几乎不可能获得谴责俄罗斯入侵乌克兰并对莫斯科实施制裁的各国政府的承诺。</p><p>出席率低将削弱北京打造其日益增长的全球影响力形象的努力。 2019 年的上一届论坛有来自 38 个国家的高级领导人参加，而 2017 年的首届论坛有 30 名国家领导人出席，特朗普政府派出了由白宫顾问率领的中层代表团参加。</p><p>中国外交部发言人没有回应置评请求。</p><p>由于项目停滞、 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-boosts-lending-to-struggling-belt-and-road-borrowers-a92d7fd?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">债务人难以偿还贷款</a>以及超支和资源配置不当的指控，“一带一路”计划面临国内外批评。西方官员指责该倡议让较贫穷的国家背负了沉重的债务——北京方面对此予以否认。一些私营企业在未能获得他们希望的好处后也失去了兴趣， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/coffee-classical-music-and-wrestling-celebrate-chinese-infrastructure-1494862432?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">早期的热议</a>促使许多企业家寻找方法将自己与该计划联系起来。</p><p> “‘一带一路’口号已经过时了，”一位与两国企业合作的新加坡商业游说人士表示，他补充说，许多企业家已经开始使用新的流行语，例如<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-on-sidelines-as-china-and-other-asia-pacific-nations-launch-trade-pact-11641038401?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">区域全面经济伙伴关系协定</a>（RCEP）——由 15 个成员国组成的亚洲贸易协定，其中中国是其成员。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="450" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824672?width=700&amp;height=450" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">雅万高铁是中国“一带一路”倡议下众多基础设施项目之一。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：任伟云/祖玛出版社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>北京方面则坚称“一带一路”有利于全球贸易和伙伴国家的发展，同时承诺改善其实施。在 2019 年论坛上，习近平承诺为“一带一路”项目引入“债务可持续性框架”，并鼓励基础设施承包遵守国际标准。中国官员还加强了风险控制，并更愿意<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/zambia-reaches-watershed-deal-on-china-debt-2392593a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">接受一些损失并重新谈判债务</a>。</p><p>随着欧洲大陆主要大国重新评估与中国的关系，欧洲在疫情爆发之前就开始背弃“一带一路”。自2019年以来，欧盟官方对华政策将北京视为“系统性竞争对手”，而不仅仅是商业伙伴。第二年，中国欧盟商会表示，欧洲企业从“一带一路”中只得到了“零碎”，因为大部分融资都是通过中国国有实体进行的。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>中国的“一带一路”倡议如何体现其全球地位和雄心？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>外交争端也让与中国建立更紧密的贸易关系变得不那么令人愉快。 2020年，中国外交官威胁称，如果捷克参议员飞往台湾这个北京声称拥有其领土的自治岛屿，就会减少从捷克共和国进口钢琴。捷克时任总统是“一带一路”的坚定支持者。这一事件引发了对中国的怀疑浪潮，帮助选举了一位欧洲最直言不讳的对华鹰派之一的新总统。</p><p>次年，在立陶宛允许台湾以暗示该岛是一个独立国家的名义开设当地办事处后<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/eu-takes-china-to-wto-over-lithuania-trade-restrictions-11643271938?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，中国从立陶宛的进口减少</a>了 80%。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/eu-files-complaint-in-wto-over-chinas-trade-retaliation-on-lithuania-11670402333" target="_blank" class="icon none">欧盟在世界贸易组织起诉中国</a>，并加大力度减少对中国的贸易依赖。</p><p>中国对俄罗斯入侵乌克兰的矛盾反应进一步疏远了许多欧洲官员，他们开始与美国更加密切地合作，以遏制北京的全球影响力——包括“一带一路”倡议。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-fellow-g-7-leaders-take-on-china-at-hiroshima-summit-573108e0" target="_blank" class="icon none">在 5 月份于广岛举行的峰会上</a>，七国集团先进民主国家建立了全球基础设施合作伙伴关系，领导人承诺为发展中国家筹集 6000 亿美元的投资。欧盟致力于动员私人和公共投资，其价值超过一半。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——罗马的玛格丽塔·斯坦卡蒂 (Margherita Stancati) 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 Chun Han Wong（ <a href="mailto:chunhan.wong@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">chunhan.wong@wsj.com）</a> 、Laurence Norman（ <a href="mailto:laurence.norman@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">laurence.norman@wsj.com</a> ）和 Drew Hinshaw（ <a href="mailto:drew.hinshaw@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">drew.hinshaw@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 16:19:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/europe-avoids-chinas-belt-and-road-forum-keeping-a-distance-from-xi-and-putin-14f6253b</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/europe-avoids-chinas-belt-and-road-forum-keeping-a-distance-from-xi-and-putin-14f6253b<author><![CDATA[Chun Han WongLaurence NormanDrew Hinshaw]]></author><category>专有的</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Niger General Declares Himself Leader, as Russian Mercenary Hails Coup]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>西方和非洲国家考虑如何应对被扣押的总统被推翻<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001093830"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=DC3DD938-33C6-4ADA-887D-E8ED2882AEA7&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fniger-general-declares-himself-leader-as-russian-mercenary-hails-coup-d47efa68&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">尼日尔总统卫队负责人周五在士兵发动政变推翻总统穆罕默德·巴祖姆后宣布自己为国家领导人。军队警告不要外国军事干预以恢复巴祖姆的地位。 Photo: Agence France-Presse/Getty Images<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001093830"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/benoit-faucon" itemprop="url" rel="author">伯努瓦·福孔</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 28 日上午 11:52 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-general-declares-himself-leader-as-russian-mercenary-hails-coup-d47efa68"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>尼日尔总统卫队负责人周五宣布自己是新军政府的领导人<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/apparent-coup-attempt-hits-u-s-ally-niger-e3efa36d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，此前他废黜了美国在非洲打击极端主义方面的重要盟友总统</a>。</p><p>与此同时，俄罗斯准军事组织瓦格纳领导人叶夫根尼·普里戈任周五对政变策划者表示欢迎，这表明俄罗斯可能寻求利用尼日尔的骚乱。</p><p>针对民选总统穆罕默德·巴祖姆的军事政变可能会破坏<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-upends-u-s-security-plans-in-west-africa-handing-russia-an-opportunity-8dcf6679?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">美国打击伊斯兰激进分子在西非扩张的战略</a>。</p><p>尼日尔总统卫队指挥官阿卜杜拉哈曼·蒂亚尼将军周五在国家电视台发表讲话时表示，他所领导的军政府于本周早些时候罢免了巴祖姆。</p><p>蒂亚尼列举了该国反恐努力中的挫折来证明巴祖姆的免职是合理的。 “如果我们不目睹我们的国家逐渐消失，我们就不能继续采取同样的做法，”他说。</p><p>但了解政变情况的人士表示，周三早些时候，蒂尼最初在总统官邸将总统劫持为人质，原因是巴祖姆计划解雇总统并减少士兵福利，引发争议。知情人士称，这场争端升级为一场未遂政变。</p><p>主要将军后来站在总统卫队一边，称他们希望避免流血。但到目前为止，尚不清楚谁将领导新军政府，局势也依然不稳定。</p><p>了解巴祖姆情况的人士称，巴祖姆拒绝辞职，并一直在官邸与西方外交官交谈。</p><p>与此同时，熟悉他情况的人士表示，将他免职的陆军将领仍在争论谁最终将统治这个国家，以及他们是否应该与俄罗斯或其雇佣军结盟。一位与总统关系密切的人士表示，总统复职“仍有一线希望”。</p><p>西方安全界担心，在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-need-of-allies-putin-courts-african-leaders-in-st-petersburg-b6596a7b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">莫斯科试图扩大自己在该地区的影响力</a>之际，针对巴祖姆的政变可能会给俄罗斯带来战略优势。巴祖姆得到了美国和法国的大规模军事和经济支持。</p><p>周四晚间，普里戈任对尼日尔的政变表示欢迎。普里戈任是上个月<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/putins-war-on-ukraine-backfires-leading-to-wagner-uprising-at-home-6530de71?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">反抗俄罗斯军队指挥部的叛乱失败的</a>幕后黑手。</p><p> “尼日尔发生的事情只不过是尼日尔人民与其殖民者的斗争，”他在 Telegram 账户上发布的语音邮件中说道。在国内叛变失败后，普里戈任表示，他希望将重点放在瓦格纳在非洲的业务上。</p><p>瓦格纳武装分子已在包括马里在内的非洲大陆四个国家站稳脚跟，并正试图进入尼日尔的三个邻国布基纳法索和乍得。西方官员表示，没有证据表明俄罗斯（已谴责策划者）或瓦格纳参与了政变。</p><p>巴祖姆于 2021 年当选，曾是美国打击基地组织和伊斯兰国运动的关键盟友，后者的暴力意识形态已从中东蔓延到撒哈拉以南的半干旱地带萨赫勒地区。最近几年。这个幅员辽阔的西非国家拥有美国无人机和美国突击队，他们训练了尼日尔特种部队，并在打击叛乱分子的战斗任务中为他们提供建议。</p><p>军政府遭到了国际社会的广泛谴责，包括地区大国尼日利亚、法国、前殖民国家和美国的谴责</p><p>联合国安理会周五召开紧急会议，决定如何应对政变。法国总统</p>埃马纽埃尔·马克龙周五呼吁在尼日尔所属的西非国家经济共同体周日举行会议时对军政府实施制裁。西非国家经济共同体曾在马里和布基纳法索政变后实施过经济和贸易限制。<p></p><p>周五，蒂亚尼表示，他将寻求与马里和布基纳法索更密切的合作，这两个国家都迫使法国执行反恐任务，并与俄罗斯走得更近。</p><p> “如果尼日尔陷入孤立并失去西方军事支持，尼日尔可能别无选择，只能求助于俄罗斯或瓦格纳，”美国苏丹问题特使前幕僚长卡梅伦·哈德森表示。他指出，圣战分子比马里和布基纳法索的圣战分子更接近首都尼亚美。</p><p>写信给 Benoit Faucon，邮箱为<a href="mailto:benoit.faucon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">benoit.faucon@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 15:52:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-general-declares-himself-leader-as- Russian-mercenary-hails-coup-d47efa68</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-general-declares-himself-leader-as- Russian-mercenary-hails-coup-d47efa68<author><![CDATA[Benoit Faucon]]></author><category>航空航天/国防</category><category>国防设备/产品</category><category>工业品</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>Armed Rebellion</category><category>武装部队</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>armed rebellion</category><category>武装部队</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</categor